  "body": "### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThis is a blocker for pyethereum Casper branch.\r\n\r\nVyper depends on [pyethereum 2.1.3](https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/blob/master/setup.py#L26), this introduces errors to the installation.\r\n\r\n```\r\nerror: ethereum 2.1.0 is installed but ethereum==2.1.3 is required by {'vyper'}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nMove pyethereum to dev_requirements.txt.\r\n\r\nThe pyethereum is mainly imported in two places of the codebase. Mostly it is imported in `scripts/`, removing it should not affect the functionality of the package. It is also imported in [parser_utils](https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/blob/master/vyper/parser/parser_utils.py#L3), which should be replaceable with constants in `vyper/opcodes`\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n![](https://i.imgur.com/EYuLW94.gif)\r\n",
